Those surveyed said that corruption, the Covid-19 pandemic, lack of access to better education and the crisis in the healthcare sector, including the strike by healthcare workers, were some of the causes of the difficulties experienced in 2020. The survey was conducted between December 27 and 29 with a margin of error of a plus/minus 3.



